            <div type="transcript" id="F94A">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Have you got a Brook in your<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 little heart,</l>
                    <l>Where bashful flowers blow, </l>
                    <l>And blushing birds go down to<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 drink - </l>
                    <l>And shadows tremble so - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>And nobody knows, so still it flows,</l>
                    <l>That any brook is there, </l>
                    <l>And yet your little draught<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 of life </l>
                    <l>Is daily drunken there - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Why - look out for the little brook<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 in March, </l>
                    <l>When the rivers overflow,</l>
                    <l>And the snows come hurrying<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 from the hills, </l>
                    <l>And the bridges often go -<app type="division"><lem><pb/></lem></app>
 </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>And <em>later,</em> in <em>August</em> it may be, </l>
                    <l>When the meadows parching lie, </l>
                    <l>Beware, lest this little brook<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 of life,</l>
                    <l>Some burning noon go dry!  </l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
